Quickly identify opportunities by determining what is contributing to sales performance.

Sales Performance Trends

Stay on top of your sales performance by viewing trends and identify key factors driving sales.

Geographic Sales Insights

View sales performance by geography; quickly identify and respond to key geographical trends.

Net PPM

Quickly identify what products are contributing to profitability by viewing: a) Net PPM b) percentage of total c) prior period d) previous year

Pre-Orders

Effectively manage new product releases by closely monitoring pre-order performance.

Traffic Diagnostic

Quickly identify changes in: a) glance views and b) conversion by viewing prior period, previous year, and industry benchmark

Real Time Sales

Enter ASIN to display real time sales data over the last 24 hours

Forecast and Inventory Planning

Prevent replenishable out of stock revenue losses with data-driven inventory planning

Inventory Health

Monitor the health of the inventory of your products through weekly updates; quickly identify and respond to unfavorable trends.

Amazon Search Terms

Discover what products are winning the most clicks and conversions on strategic search terms. Assess the impact of your marketing campaigns by monitoring trends.

Repeat Purchase Behavior

Better strategize and assess your marketing campaigns to drive repeat purchases and acquire new customers.

Market Basket Analysis

Identify cross-selling and bundling opportunities by gaining insight on products that are being purchased together by your customers.

Item Comparison and Alternate Purchase Behavior

Improve your competitive intelligence by gaining insight on products most frequently viewed together with yours in addition to customers' final choice after viewing your product.

Demographics

Connect with your target audience more effectively or identify customization opportunities with customer demographics insights.

Customer Reviews

Stay on top of customer experience by monitoring customer ratings and reviews.

Sales Diagnostic

Quickly identify opportunities by determining what is contributing to sales performance.

Key Performance Indicators.

Actual results displayed.

Comparison to preceding time frame.

Comparison to last year.

Comparison to last 90 days.

Ordered Revenue

Ordered Product Sales in the selected time frame. Adjustments are made for returns.

Ordered Units

Number of units ordered.

Average Sales Price

Average price per ordered unit.

Glance View Trend (Impressions)

Trend in Glance Views (GV).

Conversion Trend

Trend in percent of glance views that result in purchase.

Rep OOS

Replenishable Out Of Stock. Glance views the product received when it was out of stock but replenishable as a % of total product glance views.

Lost Buy Box (LBB) Price

Lost Buy Box due to price when the product is in stock.

Amazon Standard Identification Number. The unique identifier given to all products sold on Amazon.

Products with variations (size, color, etc.) have a Parent ASIN and Child ASINs. The Parent ASIN represents the generic overall product (non-purchasable).

The European Article Number (EAN) is a barcode standard, a 12- or 13-digit product identification code.

13-digit International Standard Book Number

The Universal Product Code (UPC) used for retail packaging scanning at the point of sale.
